snippet.textDisplay: While the Texans did have 24 points before KC scored. Let's be real. The Chiefs gave them 21 of those. Complete blown coverage got the first one. Man was as open as anyone, CB went the opposite way. If you can't score on that you should go home. Chiefs mistake, not Texan success. Second TD blocked punt. Fluke plain and simple. It happens in football games, yes I get that but unless your team is stacking deep double digit blocked punts you can't claim it as success. It's an error on the kicking team. Third TD. Fumbled punt catch. Again nothing the Texans did to earn that one. Ball was already on the ground when the first Texan showed up they didn't knock it out. So Technically they was only up 3 nothing cause they did earn that field goal. Play this first quarter 10 times and the Texans never get ahead more than 10 if that. Everyone acting like the Texans legit scored 24 points and then chocked. Take away the error's and the Texans only score 10 points this game. Of course not many people have the nerve to admit that 24 of their 31 points were pure luck or a lucky error in Texan favor.
